    "He initially worked as an unpaid attach\u00e9 at the National Gallery, London, and in the Department of Prints and Drawings at the British Museum.": [],
    "Cox entered graduate school at the University in Berlin, because no British university offered a degree in the subject, studying, for one semester, under the outstanding medievalist <a href=\"/goldschmidta\">Adolph Goldschmidt</a>.": [],
